# SongSage Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and update the paths for your system

# ==============================================================================
# LINUX / UBUNTU
# ==============================================================================
# BIRDNET_RESULTS_DIR=/home/username/BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra/results
# BIRDNET_AUDIO_DIR=/home/username/BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra/recordings
# BIRDNET_ANALYZER_DIR=/home/username/BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra

# ==============================================================================
# macOS / APPLE
# ==============================================================================
# BIRDNET_RESULTS_DIR=/Users/username/BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra/results
# BIRDNET_AUDIO_DIR=/Users/username/BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra/recordings
# BIRDNET_ANALYZER_DIR=/Users/username/BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra

# ==============================================================================
# WINDOWS
# ==============================================================================
# BIRDNET_RESULTS_DIR=C:\Users\username\BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra\results
# BIRDNET_AUDIO_DIR=C:\Users\username\BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra\recordings
# BIRDNET_ANALYZER_DIR=C:\Users\username\BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra

# ==============================================================================
# BIRDNET PYTHON (optional - for audio analysis)
# ==============================================================================
# If BirdNET's dependencies (TensorFlow, librosa) are installed in a
# different Python than the system default, set this to that Python path.
# Auto-detection order: BIRDNET_PYTHON env var → BirdNET venv → system python
#
# BIRDNET_PYTHON=/home/username/BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra/venv/bin/python3

# ==============================================================================
# NOTES
# ==============================================================================
# - Replace 'username' with your actual username
# - If you don't create a .env file, the system will auto-detect paths:
#   * Linux: ~/BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra or ~/BirdNET-Analyzer
#   * macOS: ~/BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra
#   * Windows: C:\Users\YourName\BirdNET-Analyzer-Sierra
# - Use forward slashes (/) or escaped backslashes (\\) in paths
# - Remove the # at the start of lines to activate them



